# Skill Pattern Reference

Pointer to the conventions every skill in this repo follows. Activate when
adding a new skill or restructuring an existing one.

## Skill folder shape

```text
<skill>/SKILL.md.tmpl   # source — edit this
<skill>/SKILL.md        # generated by scripts/gen-skill-docs.mjs
<skill>/sections/*.md.tmpl  # optional supporting templates
```

`SKILL.md` is regenerated from the `.tmpl` by `npm run build:skills`. The
generator substitutes `{{PREAMBLE}}`, `{{POLICY_REQUIREMENTS}}`, and
`{{BASE_OUTPUT_RULES}}` blocks defined in `scripts/gen-skill-docs.mjs`.

## What every skill includes

- Frontmatter: `name`, `version`, multi-line `description`.
- Enterprise preamble (via `{{PREAMBLE}}`) — scope, no public egress, policy-gated tools, scoped commits.
- Activation triggers — when to invoke.
- Workflow — concrete steps.
- Policy requirements (via `{{POLICY_REQUIREMENTS}}`).
- Output rules (via `{{BASE_OUTPUT_RULES}}`).

## After editing a skill

```bash
npm run build:skills
npm run check:skills
npm test
```

Commit `.tmpl` and generated `.md` together.

## Disabled by default

`policies/enterprise-default.json` and every profile must keep these off:

- Public telemetry, public update checks, public tunnels.
- Public web scraping, cookie/session import.
- Unscoped credential reads, global mutations, deploys, database writes.

## Registering a skill

A new skill must appear in:

- `docs/skill-catalog.md` — row in the appropriate table.
- `docs/module-map.md` — bullet under the right section.
- Relevant `profiles/*.json` if it's part of a profile.

